The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Three killed   in witch-hunt 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Three killed   in witch-hunt 
                                  
	Tezpur, Oct. 18 (UNI): Three members of a family, including a minor, were killed in an incident of witch-hunting in Sonitpur district of Assam early this morning.         
	Ghasi Santhal, his wife Kiron and their 10-year-old son Billu were killed when an armed mob attacked them at their home in Adabari tea estate near Balipara around 5am. The couples other son, Deepak, and two daughters escaped. Deepak identified two of the attackers as Umesh Gogoi and Shyam Rajak. Police have registered a case against them. They were accused of practising black magic that allegedly led to the death of a family member of Umesh.                                                                                                                                            
